#. type: Title =
#: Tool-Relight.markdown.txt:2
#, no-wrap
msgid "Relighting\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Relight.markdown.txt:7
msgid ""
"![image](images/Tool-Relight-en.png) The **Relight** tool allows you to "
"\"relight\" all or parts of your photo as if the lighting were different "
"when you took it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Relight.markdown.txt:12
msgid ""
"The Relight tool does this by reducing the large scale contrast and, at the "
"same time, increasing the local contrast. This mimics the behavior of the "
"human visual system and makes your photo more appealing and easier to work "
"with."
msgstr ""

#. type: Title -
#: Tool-Relight.markdown.txt:14
#, no-wrap
msgid "To adjust the contrast of your photo:\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Relight.markdown.txt:17
msgid "![image](images/Button-Relight.png)"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Relight.markdown.txt:33
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"1.  Click the Relight tool button in the [tool bar](Tools-Editing.html).\n"
"    (A new Relight tool will appear at the top of the [tool\n"
"    stack](Tool_Stack.html).)\n"
"2.  Use the sliders to adjust the contrast:\n"
"    -   The Shadows slider adjusts the lightness of those parts of your\n"
"        photo that are in shadow.\n"
"    -   The Highlights slider adjusts the lightness of those part of\n"
"        your photo that are brightly lit.\n"
"    -   The Detail slider controls the local contrast adjustment on the\n"
"        details in your photo. The higher the detail value, the higher\n"
"        the detail.\n"
"    -   The Depth slider adjusts how \"flat\" or \"deep\" the lighting of\n"
"        your photo is.\n"
"    -   The Fuzz slider adjusts how \"fuzzy\" the edges between light and\n"
"        dark areas are.\n"
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: Tool-Relight.markdown.txt:40
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"3.  Optionally:\n"
"    -   Create a mask using [regions](Regions.html).\n"
"    -   Select a different [blend mode](Blend_Modes.html).\n"
"    -   Adjust the [Opacity slider](Tool_Anatomy.html#Opacity).\n"
"    -   Make a [color/luminosity](Color_Luminosity_Selection.html)\n"
"        selection.\n"
msgstr ""

